article.headline: Denver 72, South Alabama 67
article.story: MOBILE, Ala. (AP) -- Antonio Porch had 25 points and 11 rebounds to lead Denver to a 72-67 victory over South Alabama on Thursday night. Yemi Nicholson had 20 points and 10 rebounds for Denver (11-6, 6-0 Sun Belt Conference) and Brett Seger scored 13 points. Richard Law scored a career-high 25 points for South Alabama (5-13, 2-5) and was 6-of-10 from 3-point range. Mario Jointer had 14 points and 10 rebounds for the Jaguars. South Alabama trailed for most of the game but took the lead on a 3-pointer by Law with 3:39 left. But Nicholson scored on an offensive rebound and Seger hit a 3 to give Denver a four-point lead. Law hit another 3-pointer to make it 68-67 with 42 seconds remaining, but Denver scored the final four points of the game. Denver shot 42.6 percent from the field and South Alabama shot 44.1 percent.
